# Trendyol Code Patterns

## Auth Pattern

```
credentials = base64(apiKey + ":" + apiSecret)
Authorization: Basic {credentials}
X-Supplier-Id: {sellerId}           // numeric string
storefrontCode: {storefrontCode}    // "1" for TR, country code for GLOBAL
```

For language-specific code: call `generateImplementationGuide(moduleKey, language)`.

## Async Batch Pattern

Every mutation endpoint is asynchronous. Response: `{ "batchRequestId": "..." }`.

```
1. Send mutation → capture batchRequestId → store it
2. Poll getBatchRequestResult every 3-5 seconds (max 10 attempts)
3. Stop when status == "COMPLETED"
4. COMPLETED ≠ success — inspect items[].status
5. Collect items where status == "FAILED" → log failureReasons
6. Retry ONLY failed items — never retry entire batch
7. Store full result within 4 hours (results expire)
```

For endpoint-specific strategy: `getBatchPollingStrategy(endpointKey)`.
For language-specific polling: `generateImplementationGuide(moduleKey, language)`.

## updatePriceAndInventory — 15-Minute Deduplication

Same request (same barcodes, same values) cannot be sent within 15 minutes.

```
Before sending:
  for each item:
    lastSent = store.get(item.barcode)
    if lastSent exists AND minutesSince < 15 AND values unchanged:
      skip this item

After sending:
  for each sent item:
    store.set(item.barcode, { timestamp: now(), values: {...} })
```

Changing any field value resets the window.

## batchRequestType Reference

| Endpoint | batchRequestType |
|---|---|
| createProducts | ProductV2OnBoarding |
| updateUnapproved/Content/Variant/Delivery | ProductV2Update |
| updatePriceAndInventory | ProductInventoryUpdate |
| archiveProducts, unlockProducts | ProductArchiveUpdate |
| deleteProducts | ProductDeletion |

## Code Quality Checklist

All generated implementation code must satisfy:

- [ ] Base URL configurable (env var or config) — never hardcoded
- [ ] Credentials from configuration — never hardcoded
- [ ] storefrontCode configurable per marketplace
- [ ] Batch results stored before 4-hour expiry
- [ ] Failed items collected separately for retry
- [ ] 15-minute deduplication implemented for updatePriceAndInventory
- [ ] Polling handles timeout (max 10 attempts)
- [ ] Item-level status inspected after COMPLETED